[
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Then answered Eliphaz the Temanite, and said,",
    "hash": "86d7ab4f0d97c149a8d8b63bbc36b8d1815e9e790512555d110f2cf2ab1f7904"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Should a wise man utter vain knowledge, and fill his belly with the east wind? {vain...: Heb. knowledge of wind}",
    "hash": "bb0469bcc2b49c94982849866430a0ef0c47a3b2a65e14c4fc5dd5178e010bda"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Should he reason with unprofitable talk? or with speeches wherewith he can do no good?",
    "hash": "7668ec8d227bfcef3793439e50757a37fefee551b72d33d509290bad87097494"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Yea, thou castest off fear, and restrainest prayer before God. {castest...: Heb. makest void} {prayer: or, speech}",
    "hash": "f2fa8e3f7b8a129f1fd7a8607e04acc987e6d823df6ab98f03ccc3a695005dc4"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "For thy mouth uttereth thine iniquity, and thou choosest the tongue of the crafty. {uttereth: Heb. teacheth}",
    "hash": "04794148a80881dcdd7f890f5fc24679aacd0abd219070befaef9bbacd6c9d79"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Thine own mouth condemneth thee, and not I: yea, thine own lips testify against thee.",
    "hash": "3c56ba31995a6e304f3064aa121e0685684f96a00dae566a91a15e4f9c205a86"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "{Art} thou the first man {that} was born? or wast thou made before the hills?",
    "hash": "901a00ea5ea7a4522258638583b05f392d811160d508f5bcb847b17695365eec"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Hast thou heard the secret of God? and dost thou restrain wisdom to thyself?",
    "hash": "fac45881498ac4e9c93ea78f80cc8f2b36cb9d3cac95cbb0dc5f28d51ab66cab"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "What knowest thou, that we know not? {what} understandest thou, which {is} not in us?",
    "hash": "65dd931324687e5669b0a672e7ae1e9e0191e1713b7d4c0022c20deb0018af3a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "With us {are} both the grayheaded and very aged men, much elder than thy father.",
    "hash": "a47b7f8fd95af8aa9f4a7b8265562bd9420c436dcbade3186c2a69e64919241a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "{Are} the consolations of God small with thee? is there any secret thing with thee?",
    "hash": "6c4f40830fb9c48bf659df446411d91c5134a18c60e6517b39ff785150056ec6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Why doth thine heart carry thee away? and what do thy eyes wink at,",
    "hash": "abc9a3be6e91a5f14444cc2a7373601c9f1777d424731c18c17a239cc2436829"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "That thou turnest thy spirit against God, and lettest {such} words go out of thy mouth?",
    "hash": "b956010744b2a2178f4a29251b00f7cb08678411e62baf010bc4f7eff760b4fc"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "What {is} man, that he should be clean? and {he which is} born of a woman, that he should be righteous?",
    "hash": "9c15c97abfc92c559f00449586a0182aeca92e55c2ecb7cdcb5fcebdbd39ffba"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Behold, he putteth no trust in his saints; yea, the heavens are not clean in his sight.",
    "hash": "93a469dca0eedb3c5d93b4fad34eb10d7d05c58737bcad584bbae43656a21b74"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "How much more abominable and filthy {is} man, which drinketh iniquity like water?",
    "hash": "4602d4e8437e5cc338aeeebb902803cafe0864c0be1b7a4e1e986c75954c26f6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "I will shew thee, hear me; and that {which} I have seen I will declare;",
    "hash": "d67d996f2af5576e0472e54532023913ac0be6e1ea278d17c7f3400306261bc6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Which wise men have told from their fathers, and have not hid {it}:",
    "hash": "34269c01107352a26f7deb0db864d23abd1a336e59aca1ce13a2e45115ff9957"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Unto whom alone the earth was given, and no stranger passed among them.",
    "hash": "cc17600250b882aee8a13e58dc9d3799a3e6bdd9f1d204c65b895a12050ac786"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "The wicked man travaileth with pain all {his} days, and the number of years is hidden to the oppressor.",
    "hash": "f42f0d0fe93b0ed9130c1a992300337ab06d8efc33ff3e3d03418fd086360714"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "A dreadful sound {is} in his ears: in prosperity the destroyer shall come upon him. {A dreadful...: Heb. A sound of fears}",
    "hash": "c965b1dd3d3d2d340d0d814cfd2be366bbd76bb5c7292dc03a8ca53c30a03396"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "He believeth not that he shall return out of darkness, and he is waited for of the sword.",
    "hash": "696d6f02b360cb5c395821ee46d944f5791b159477374fffee4fad6a2268f2fd"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "He wandereth abroad for bread, {saying}, Where {is it}? he knoweth that the day of darkness is ready at his hand.",
    "hash": "6beba1bfc74608199ed4a3aba6a8306eb368bd1197c62650e64ac55266fce8e0"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Trouble and anguish shall make him afraid; they shall prevail against him, as a king ready to the battle.",
    "hash": "1df2e3b601022d8a7abebda027f932d2f34a217c54a7a6df9e4cb92e26d1c1df"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.25",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "For he stretcheth out his hand against God, and strengtheneth himself against the Almighty.",
    "hash": "01ba6b2c92a34414672b0fe9f2820b3d8a8145b357094f463216bc7ebdef922b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.26",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "He runneth upon him, {even} on {his} neck, upon the thick bosses of his bucklers:",
    "hash": "1fceac3b23202a1b21eb7b46f2ec161bde5523308c9d064bbad8a4b25a245277"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.27",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Because he covereth his face with his fatness, and maketh collops of fat on {his} flanks.",
    "hash": "541ee3c871156b03cc07f06b365792d0c20dc719b7a2c9590504197194abac5d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.28",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "And he dwelleth in desolate cities, {and} in houses which no man inhabiteth, which are ready to become heaps.",
    "hash": "ba5363b7c5beb3b966d6807aeafcd318fa37dd4e0579d3d87e5d2d5ca14e9f8b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.29",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "He shall not be rich, neither shall his substance continue, neither shall he prolong the perfection thereof upon the earth.",
    "hash": "9b61d8c9db459e38e110ed692d2c0c1e1b31c782b2a3caaddde00cd5dced201f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.30",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "He shall not depart out of darkness; the flame shall dry up his branches, and by the breath of his mouth shall he go away.",
    "hash": "77b74fe484d12ce88ef6609725e8460c0f5d60be8196fbc862834694d0904000"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.31",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "Let not him that is deceived trust in vanity: for vanity shall be his recompence.",
    "hash": "505efc0f0a6cfae7d7d0eb43e18b7a31725acbd714c15b3140b3bf9195d5e358"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.32",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "It shall be accomplished before his time, and his branch shall not be green. {accomplished: or, cut off}",
    "hash": "aeb465bf1a3694df3af6b657b2a9da2cc62a2566effcc5899ef21b770e6c298d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.33",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "He shall shake off his unripe grape as the vine, and shall cast off his flower as the olive.",
    "hash": "1c98a90c7ec8f97a7cf8232a519f6788a73687d0bed0b872b7466a6efdbe797b"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.34",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "For the congregation of hypocrites {shall be} desolate, and fire shall consume the tabernacles of bribery.",
    "hash": "b41ccd2f57e00353cd555382708374af47512f4531405c7ea027cf30936df428"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.15.35",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "They conceive mischief, and bring forth vanity, and their belly prepareth deceit. {vanity: or, iniquity}",
    "hash": "3a01c31fd992ed7a923e109d232695c76b0a67a644e0d630c4c57881b24a0860"
  }
]